{"title":"UK Brand Ribble Launches Gravel Bike Line Including Titanium Model","link":"https://theradavist.com/2021/03/uk-brand-ribble-launches-gravel-bike-line-including-titanium-model/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=uk-brand-ribble-launches-gravel-bike-line-including-titanium-model","date":1617191439000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1042\" height=\"695\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/RibbleTitaniumGravel.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-208021\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/RibbleTitaniumGravel.jpg?w=1042&amp;quality=75 1042w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/RibbleTitaniumGravel.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/RibbleTitaniumGravel.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/RibbleTitaniumGravel.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1042px) 100vw, 1042px\" /></p>\n<p>Ribble, the UK bicycle manufacturer, just announced their new gravel lineup which includes <a href=\"https://www.ribblecycles.co.uk/ribble-gravel-al/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">aluminum builds</a>, <a href=\"https://www.ribblecycles.co.uk/ribble-gravel-sl/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">carbon builds</a>, and this <a href=\"https://www.ribblecycles.co.uk/ribble-gravel-ti/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">titanium model</a>. Each material comes in a few build tiers, ranging from GRX 400 to GRX 810 and Campagnolo Ekar on the higher end models. </p>\n<p>The model shown here is the Titanium frame with GRX 600 and retails for $2,985.38. See the full gravel lineup at <a href=\"https://www.ribblecycles.co.uk/gravel-range/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Ribble</a>.</p>","author":"prolly","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"b68285b56d4c2a808b2130a4ef0032c7acd0177f07aa54fb9664971faa6dc204","category":"Cycling"}